<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 8:48AM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern
Roosevelt, southern Sheridan, northeastern Dawson and Richland
Counties through 945 AM MDT...
At 848 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 10 miles east of Froid to 12 miles north of
Richey. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sidney, Culbertson, Fairview, Bainville, Fort Union Trading Post,
Savage, Lambert, East Fairview, Snowden, Enid, Nohly, Wooley, Fort
Union, Crane, Mccabe and Midway.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
